name: Dodge M4S Turbo Interceptor
description:
2048 x 3072 (2:3 ratio)
#004 in "Cinema Cars" collection

Six copies were made for use in the film: two stunt cars made from molds of the original car and four non-drivable "dummies" that were destroyed during filming. During production, the real Dodge Turbo Interceptor was used in close-ups. That original was located at the Walter P. Chrysler Museum in Auburn Hills, MI until 2016, when the museum closed permanently.
